Simple log to document steps setting up a package repo on github and link it to posit.cloud

I. setup git and posit cloud
* create github repo (i.e. ansperf at org github)
* create new project in posit.cloud selecting "from github"
* on posit.cloud: rename project.Rproj to packagename.Rproj
* on posit.cloud: need to install utility packages
  + install.packages(c("roxygen2","devtools","usethis","testthat", "pkgdown"))
  + install.packages("tidyverse", "arrow")
* configure package
  + usethis::use_description(fields = list(Package = "ansperf"))
  + usethis::edit_file("DESCRIPTION") # edit as appropriate
* setup environment
  + Tools >> Project Options >> Build Tools
  + select Package (from drop-down)
  + select Create documentation with Roxygen, activate all options
  + OK and close Project Options
* go to Build tab (after posit.cloud restarted and shows it)

hook up posit.cloud and github with PAT
* run to check: usethis::git_siterep()
  then walk through it to clean the configs
* (if needed, set) usethis::use_git_config(user.name = "as-appropriate", user.email = "whatevername@org")
* usethis::git_vaccinate() # good practice shielding specs
* setup PAT
  + usethis::create_github_token() 
  +  gitcreds::gitcreds_set() # paste token, gitcreds installed with {usethis}

setup packagedown
* Run once to configure your package to use pkgdown
  usethis::use_pkgdown()
* (modify _pkgdown.yml)
* setup pkgdown workflow: usethis::use_pkgdown_github_pages()
* usethis::use_readme_rmd()

create functions
* usethis::use_r("function-name-file")
* CTRL+SHIFT+b (to build package)
* CTRL+SHIFT+l (to load and test function)

To build a Source Package do the following:

    Create a new folder tmp
    devtools::build(path = "tmp")
    The resulting file, e.g. mypkg_0.0.0.9000.tar.gz can be downloaded to your computer.
